# Toofies — environment variables (EXAMPLE / template — safe to commit).
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Copy this file to `.env.local`  →  cp .env.example .env.local
#   2. Fill in the real values in `.env.local`.
#   3. `.env.local` is git-ignored and MUST NEVER be committed. Never paste real
#      keys into git, chat, or any client code. This example file stays keyless.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase — client / on-device (Expo reads EXPO_PUBLIC_* into the app bundle)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The Project URL and the ANON (publishable) key are DESIGNED to ship in the app
# and are protected by Row-Level Security. Get them from:
#   Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API → Project URL / anon public key
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase — SERVER ONLY  (⚠️ never in the mobile app, never committed)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The service_role key BYPASSES Row-Level Security and has full database access.
# It belongs ONLY in a trusted server/backend or EAS/CI secret store — never in
# the client bundle, never in `.env.local` for the app, never in git.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
